# Entrust DV TLS Issuing RSA CA 2 — intermediate certificate
#
# Why this is vendored:
#   asmdc.org serves a BROKEN certificate chain: its leaf (*.asmdc.org) is
#   issued by "Entrust DV TLS Issuing RSA CA 2", but the server sends the wrong
#   intermediate ("Entrust Certification Authority - L1K"), so the chain can't
#   be built and TLS verification fails. Rather than disable verification, we
#   supply the correct intermediate ourselves and verify against certifi's
#   roots + this cert. The intermediate chains to "Sectigo Public Server
#   Authentication Root R46", which IS in the standard CA bundle.
#
# Provenance:
#   Downloaded from the leaf's Authority Information Access (CA Issuers) URL:
#   http://crt.sectigo.com/EntrustDVTLSIssuingRSACA2.crt
#   SHA-256: EC:37:DF:84:99:95:A5:30:89:C9:8B:D1:2E:CA:C7:74:06:A2:B4:14:78:77:9E:5C:B8:2C:5F:16:6E:7D:F8:3C
#   Subject: C=CA, O=Entrust Limited, CN=Entrust DV TLS Issuing RSA CA 2
#   Issuer:  C=GB, O=Sectigo Limited, CN=Sectigo Public Server Authentication Root R46
#   Not After: 2027-12-10  (re-vendor before this date if asmdc.org's chain is still broken)
